| react-leaflet       | React bindings for Leaflet maps            |

## Deployment (Railway — PaaS)

The application is deployed as a single service on Railway. The Express
backend serves both the API and the React static build, so only one
service is needed.

### Environment

- Platform: Railway (free tier)
- Runtime: Node.js 22 (via Docker `node:22-slim`)
- Database: SQLite (ephemeral — reseeds on every deploy)
- Build: Custom Dockerfile at project root

### How it works

1. The `Dockerfile` installs dependencies for both frontend and backend.
2. The frontend is built with `npm run build` (Vite outputs to `frontend/dist/`).
3. Prisma client is generated at build time.
4. At container startup (`CMD`), the database is created (`prisma db push`),
   seeded (`prisma db seed`), and then the Express server starts.
5. Express serves the API on its normal routes and the React static build
   on all other GET requests (SPA fallback).

### Railway deployment steps

1. Create a Railway account at https://railway.com and link your GitHub repo.
2. Create a new project and add a service pointed at the repository root.
3. Railway will auto-detect the `Dockerfile` and `railway.json` config.
4. Set the following environment variables in the Railway service settings:

   ```
   JWT_SECRET=<strong-random-hex-string>
   FRONTEND_URL=https://<your-app>.up.railway.app
   NODE_ENV=production
   PORT=3000
   ```

5. Generate a domain under the service's Settings > Networking > Public Networking.
   Use port 3000 for the domain.
6. Deploy. Railway builds the Docker image and starts the container.
7. The database seeds automatically on every deploy/restart.

### Current deployment

- URL: https://dentalink-production-ceda.up.railway.app
- The SQLite database and uploaded files are ephemeral (reset on redeploy).
  This is acceptable per A3 requirements.

## Alternative: Manual Deployment (Ubuntu VPS / EC2)

If deploying to a bare VM instead of Railway:

1. Provision an Ubuntu 24.04 instance (e.g., AWS EC2 free tier).
2. Install Node.js 22.x:
   ```bash
   curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_22.x | sudo -E bash -
   sudo apt-get install -y nodejs
   ```
3. Clone the repo and follow the "Local Development Setup" steps above.
4. Set `NODE_ENV=production` and `FRONTEND_URL=http://<your-ip>:3000`.
5. Build the frontend:
   ```bash
   cd frontend && npm install && npm run build && cd ..
   ```
6. Start with PM2:
   ```bash
   sudo npm install -g pm2
   cd backend
   npx prisma generate && npx prisma db push && npx prisma db seed
   pm2 start src/server.js -- 3000
   pm2 save && pm2 startup
   ```
7. (Optional) Set up Nginx as a reverse proxy on port 80/443 and use
   Certbot for HTTPS.
 etc) etc)